<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1690,2039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">
Two 
<typeStatus box="[255,338,1763,1787]" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">syntype</typeStatus>
specimens, one male and one female, were located. These correspond to the two specimens 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorham, H. S." pageId="2" pageNumber="386" pagination="29 - 65" refId="ref6258" refString="Gorham, H. S. (1881) Insecta. Coleoptera. Malacodermata. Lampyridae. Biologia Centrali-Americana, 3 (2), 29 - 65." type="journal article" year="1881">Gorham (1881)</bibRefCitation>
examined. There was an additional specimen located with a 
<typeStatus box="[875,958,1799,1823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">syntype</typeStatus>
label, however we believe this to be in error as the locality does not match that which 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorham, H. S." box="[599,765,1835,1859]" pageId="2" pageNumber="386" pagination="29 - 65" refId="ref6258" refString="Gorham, H. S. (1881) Insecta. Coleoptera. Malacodermata. Lampyridae. Biologia Centrali-Americana, 3 (2), 29 - 65." type="journal article" year="1881">Gorham (1881)</bibRefCitation>
listed. The male specimen, bearing several type labels, is designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[304,405,1871,1895]" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The female is designated as a 
<typeStatus box="[733,880,1871,1895]" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">paralectotype</typeStatus>
. Labels for the designated 
<typeStatus box="[1164,1262,1871,1895]" pageId="2" pageNumber="386">lectotype</typeStatus>
specimen are as follows:
